            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <const/>
              <description>Tests whether the currently copied block can be pasted into the currently selected block. Returns true if it can be pasted or false otherwise.</description>
              <name>canPaste</name>
              <operation>Make sure this view has a model, the copy pointer is not null, and the block factory project types match.</operation>
              <operation>If this view's current index is not a null pointer and the copied block's type is contained within the current block's build list then return true, else return false.</operation>
              <return_description>True if the currently copied block can be pasted into the currently selected block or false if it cannot.</return_description>
              <type>bool</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Sets a new block model for this block view, releasing but not deleting any previous model set to it. If a null pointer is given this view is set to empty. This block view does not take ownership of the given model.</description>
              <name>setModel</name>
              <operation>If this view already had a model then disconnect its and its selection model's signals.</operation>
              <operation>Set the new model for this view and reset its current index to invalid.</operation>
              <operation>Check to see if the new model is a null pointer.</operation>
              <operation>Reset this view's factory and selection model pointers to null.</operation>
              <operation>Else the given pointer is not null and this view's new model is real.</operation>
              <operation>Set the block factory and selection model pointers of this view.</operation>
              <operation>Connect all selection model and model signals to this view.</operation>
              <operation>Update this object's view and context menu.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description>Pointer to the new block model this block view will display for editing.</description>
                <initializer></initializer>
                <name>model</name>
                <type>BlockModel*</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
          </function>
        </access>
        <access>
          <data>
            <type>private slots:</type>
          </data>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Called when an add action is triggered. If this object has a model then this inserts a new block of the given type in the currently selected block.</description>
              <name>addTriggered</name>
              <operation>Make sure this view has a model.</operation>
              <operation>Insert a new block of the given type into this view's model with its current index, updating its current index and context menu.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description>The block type created and inserted into this object's model if it has one.</description>
                <initializer></initializer>
                <name>type</name>
                <type>int</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Called when the remove action is triggered. If this object has a valid current index then it is removed from its model.</description>
              <name>removeTriggered</name>
              <operation>Make sure this view's current index is valid.</operation>
              <operation>Remove the currently selected index from its model, updating this view's current index and context menu.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Called when the edit action is triggered. If this object has a valid current index then this will open an edit dialog of the index's block.</description>
              <name>editTriggered</name>
              <operation>Make sure this view's current index is valid.</operation>
              <operation>Get the block pointer from the current index and make sure it is not null.</operation>
              <operation>Make a new edit dialog from the block pointer and make sure it is not null.</operation>
              <operation>Initialize the edit dialog and then execute it.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Called when the cut action is triggered. If this object has a valid current index then this will cut it from this object's model.</description>
              <name>cutTriggered</name>
              <operation>Make sure this view's current index is valid.</operation>
              <operation>Delete any existing block copy. SPECIAL NOTE: This view's copy pointer must be set to null before a new block is cut from the model or else a dead copy pointer will cause a segmentation fault.</operation>
              <operation>Cut the current index's block from its model, updating this view's index and context menu.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Called when the copy action is triggered. If this object has a valid current index then this will copy it from this object's model.</description>
              <name>copyTriggered</name>
              <operation>Make sure this view's current index is valid.</operation>
              <operation>Delete any existing block copy.</operation>
              <operation>Copy the current index's block from its model, updating this view's actions.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Called when the paste action is triggered. If this object can paste its copied block into its model then it does so.</description>
              <name>pasteTriggered</name>
              <operation>If pasting is possible then insert a new copy of the copied block into this view's model at the current index.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Called when the move up action is triggered. If this object has a valid current index then this will move it up by one.</description>
              <name>moveUpTriggered</name>
              <operation>If this view's current index is valid then move it up by one and update it.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Called when the move down action is triggered. If this object has a valid current index then this will move it down by one.</description>
              <name>moveDownTriggered</name>
              <operation>If this view's current index is valid then move it down by one and update it.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Called when this object's selection model has changed. This determines its object's new current index, updating its view and context menu afterwords.</description>
              <name>selectionModelChanged</name>
              <operation>This does not care what was deselected.</operation>
              <operation>Update this view's current index, setting it to invalid to no indexes are selected.</operation>
              <operation>Update this object's view and context menu.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description>List of indexes that have been selected by the user.</description>
                <initializer></initializer>
                <name>selected</name>
                <type>const QItemSelection&amp;</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description>Unused list of indexes that have been deselected by the user.</description>
                <initializer></initializer>
                <name>deselected</name>
                <type>const QItemSelection&amp;</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Called when this object's block model is about to be deleted. This clears its object's view to a null state and all internal pointers.</description>
              <name>modelDestroyed</name>
              <operation>Clear this view's title.</operation>
              <operation>Reset this view as empty with no model.</operation>
              <operation>Update this object's view and context menu.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Called when data in this object's block model has changed. If this object's current index is the one updated then this updates its object's view depending on the given roles.</description>
              <name>modelDataChanged</name>
              <operation>This does not care about the bottom right because this view works as a single selection model.</operation>
              <operation>Make sure the index whose data has changed is the current index and it is valid.</operation>
              <operation>Update this view's title if needed, detailed view if needed, and context menu.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description>The top left index of the rectangle of indexes whose data has changed.</description>
                <initializer></initializer>
                <name>topLeft</name>
                <type>const QModelIndex&amp;</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description>The bottom right index of the rectangle of indexes whose data has changed. This is not used in this view because only one index can change at a time.</description>
                <initializer></initializer>
                <name>bottomRight</name>
                <type>const QModelIndex&amp;</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description>The list of data roles that has changed.</description>
                <initializer></initializer>
                <name>roles</name>
                <type>const QVector&lt;int>&amp;</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Called when this object's tree view is requesting a context menu because of a right mouse click. This updates its object's current index based off the mouse click position and executes its object's context menu.</description>
              <name>contextMenuRequested</name>
              <operation>Update this view's current index based off the given position, updating the view and context menu afterwords.</operation>
              <operation>Execute this object's context menu at the mouse's current position.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description>The relative position within this object's tree view where the mouse event occurred.</description>
                <initializer></initializer>
                <name>position</name>
                <type>const QPoint&amp;</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
          </function>
        </access>
        <access>
          <data>
            <type>private:</type>
          </data>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Updates this object's detailed view using its current index. This does not update this object's title.</description>
              <name>updateView</name>
              <operation>Delete any current view of this object.</operation>
              <operation>Make sure this view's current index is valid.</operation>
              <operation>Get the block pointer of the current index and make sure it is not null.</operation>
              <operation>Make a new view from the block pointer and make sure it is not null.</operation>
              <operation>Set this object's detailed view and update its title.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Updates this object's current index using its selection model. This does not update this object's actions or context menu.</description>
              <name>updateIndex</name>
              <operation>Get the list of selected indexes from this view's selection model.</operation>
              <operation>Set this view's current index to the first index in the list or invalid if the list is empty.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Updates this object's context menu based off its current index, updating its actions beforehand as well.</description>
              <name>updateContextMenu</name>
              <operation>Update this view's actions and clear its context menu's add menu.</operation>
              <operation>Populate the context menu's add menu with this view's add actions, disabling it if there are no actions.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Updates this object's list of actions, enabling or disabling the primary ones and rebuilding the list of add actions based off the current index.</description>
              <name>updateActions</name>
              <operation>Update the add actions for this view.</operation>
              <operation>Enable or disable all actions of this view dependent on the current index being valid or not.</operation>
              <operation>Enable or disable all remaining actions of this view.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Updates the add actions list of this object, clearing out the old list and building it again based on this object's current index.</description>
              <name>updateAddActions</name>
              <operation>Delete all previous add actions of this view.</operation>
              <operation>Make sure this view has a model.</operation>
              <operation>Get the block pointer from this view's current index and make sure it is not null.</operation>
              <operation>Iterate through the build list of the block pointer, adding a new action for each block type in the list.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Updates this object's title bar based on the given block's info. If the given pointer is null then the title is cleared.</description>
              <name>updateTitle</name>
              <operation>Clear this view's current title.</operation>
              <operation>Make sure the given pointer is not null.</operation>
              <operation>Set this view's new title using the icon and display name of the given block.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description>Pointer to the block whose icon and display name is used for the title if it is not null.</description>
                <initializer></initializer>
                <name>block</name>
                <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Constructs and initializes all GUI elements for this widget.</description>
              <name>setupGui</name>
              <operation>Setup the tree view, area, actions, and menu for this new view.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Constructs and initializes the tree view of this new widget, adding it to this qt splitter.</description>
              <name>setupTreeView</name>
              <operation>Create and initialize the tree view for this object.</operation>
              <operation>Connect the context menu requested signal and add the tree view to this object's splitter.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Constructs and initializes the title and detailed view area of this new widget, adding it to the qt splitter.</description>
              <name>setupArea</name>
              <operation>Create and initialize the scroll area for this view.</operation>
              <operation>Create a new vertical layout, adding the title bar then spacing and then the new scroll area.</operation>
              <operation>Add the new layout to this object's splitter as a widget.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Constructs and initializes a new title bar for this new widget, returning a layout of the new title bar.</description>
              <name>setupTitleBar</name>
              <operation>Create the title icon label for this view.</operation>
              <operation>Create and initialize the title text label for this view.</operation>
              <operation>Create a new horizontal layout, adding the title icon label then the title text label and then a stretch.</operation>
              <operation>Return the title bar layout.</operation>
              <return_description>Pointer to layout of the new title bar.</return_description>
              <type>QLayout*</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Constructs and initializes all actions for this new widget object's context menu, excluding the add actions because they are rebuilt dynamically.</description>
              <name>setupActions</name>
              <operation>Create and initialize the remove action for this view.</operation>
              <operation>Create and initialize the edit action for this view.</operation>
              <operation>Create and initialize the cut action for this view.</operation>
              <operation>Create and initialize the copy action for this view.</operation>
              <operation>Create and initialize the paste action for this view.</operation>
              <operation>Create and initialize the move up action for this view.</operation>
              <operation>Create and initialize the move down action for this view.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Constructs and initializes the context menu for this new widget, excluding the add menu because it is rebuilt dynamically.</description>
              <name>setupMenu</name>
              <operation>Create the context menu for this view.</operation>
              <operation>Add the add menu to the context menu.</operation>
              <operation>Add all other actions to the context menu.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <constexpr/>
              <description>The width and height of icons, in pixels, presented in this object's tree view of blocks.</description>
              <initializer>32</initializer>
              <name>_titleIconSize</name>
              <static/>
              <type>int</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>Pointer to a copied block that any instance of this class can use to paste into their current block model if possible.</description>
              <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
              <name>_copy</name>
              <static/>
              <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>Pointer to this object's scroll area used to contain its detailed view widget.</description>
              <initializer></initializer>
              <name>_area</name>
              <type>QScrollArea*</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>Pointer to this object's tree view that displays the full list of its current block model.</description>
              <initializer></initializer>
              <name>_treeView</name>
              <type>QTreeView*</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>Pointer to this object's current block model.</description>
              <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
              <name>_model</name>
              <type>BlockModel*</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>Pointer to the abstract block factory for the project type of this object's currently set block model.</description>
              <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
              <name>_factory</name>
              <type>const AbstractBlockFactory*</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>Pointer the selection model of this object's tree view.</description>
              <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
              <name>_selectionModel</name>
              <type>QItemSelectionModel*</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>The currently selected model index of this object.</description>
              <initializer></initializer>
              <name>_current</name>
              <type>QModelIndex</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>Pointer to this object's title icon label used as part of the title bar above the detailed view.</description>
              <initializer></initializer>
              <name>_titleIcon</name>
              <type>QLabel*</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>Pointer to this object's title text label used as part of the title bar above the detailed view.</description>
              <initializer></initializer>
              <name>_titleText</name>
              <type>QLabel*</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>Pointer to this object's current detailed view widget, if any.</description>
              <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
              <name>_view</name>
              <type>QWidget*</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>Pointer list of this object's currently available add actions used for adding new blocks to the current index.</description>
              <initializer></initializer>
              <name>_addActions</name>
              <type>QList&lt;QAction*></type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>Pointer to this object's remove action.</description>
              <initializer></initializer>
              <name>_removeAction</name>
              <type>QAction*</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>Pointer to this object's edit action.</description>
              <initializer></initializer>
              <name>_editAction</name>
              <type>QAction*</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>Pointer to this object's cut action.</description>
              <initializer></initializer>
              <name>_cutAction</name>
              <type>QAction*</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>Pointer to this object's copy action.</description>
              <initializer></initializer>
              <name>_copyAction</name>
              <type>QAction*</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>Pointer to this object's paste action.</description>
              <initializer></initializer>
              <name>_pasteAction</name>
              <type>QAction*</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>Pointer to this object's move up action.</description>
              <initializer></initializer>
              <name>_moveUpAction</name>
              <type>QAction*</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>Pointer to this object's move down action.</description>
              <initializer></initializer>
              <name>_moveDownAction</name>
              <type>QAction*</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>Pointer to this object's add menu used as a sub menu within the context menu for listing add actions.</description>
              <initializer></initializer>
              <name>_addMenu</name>
              <type>QMenu*</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
          <variable>
            <data>
              <description>Pointer to this object's context menu.</description>
              <initializer></initializer>
              <name>_contextMenu</name>
              <type>QMenu*</type>
            </data>
          </variable>
        </access>
      </class>
      <class>
        <data>
          <description>This is the main window for the program. This class can contain an open class along with providing a menu bar for the user. Each window can contain only one project, but multiple instance windows of this class can exist in the program. When the last main window is deleted this program exits.

The menu bar provided by this class window contains the file, edit, settings, and help menus. The file menu provides basic actions for the window. These basic actions include creating a new project, opening a project, saving a project, opening the properties of an open project, scanning the source files of an open project, closing an open project, and exiting a main window.

The edit menu is the context menu of the block view class. The settings menu is the global settings for each project type. Lastly the help menu currently just provides an about dialog.</description>
          <name>MainWindow</name>
          <qtobject/>
        </data>
        <parent>
          <data>
            <access>public</access>
            <class>QMainWindow</class>
          </data>
        </parent>
        <access>
          <data>
            <type>public:</type>
          </data>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Constructs a new main window with the optional parent.</description>
              <explicit/>
              <name>^</name>
              <operation>Create this window's GUI and restore the state and geometry of the main window and its block view.</operation>
              <operation>Update this window's title and actions.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type></type>
            </data>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description>Optional parent for this new main window.</description>
                <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
                <name>parent</name>
                <type>QWidget*</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Sets the given project as this main window's new project, deleting any previous project this window may contain. This window takes ownership of any new project given to it. A null pointer can be given which means this window will have no project.</description>
              <name>setProject</name>
              <operation>Delete any previous project this window may contain and set the new project.</operation>
              <operation>Update this window's title and actions.</operation>
              <operation>Check to see if the new project for this window is a null pointer.</operation>
              <operation>Set the project's parent to this window, updating this this window's block view and updating its modification state.</operation>
              <operation>Connect all of the new project signals.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description></description>
                <initializer></initializer>
                <name>project</name>
                <type>Soc::Ut::QPtr&lt;Project>&amp;&amp;</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
          </function>
        </access>
        <access>
          <data>
            <type>protected:</type>
          </data>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Implements _QWidget_ interface. This implementation determines if it is OK to close the window and accept the event or not and ignore it.</description>
              <final/>
              <name>closeEvent</name>
              <operation>Check to see if it is OK to close this window's project.</operation>
              <operation>Save the geometry and state of this window and its block view and accept the close event.</operation>
              <operation>Else it is not OK to close this window to ignore the close event.</operation>
              <override/>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
              <virtual/>
            </data>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description>See Qt docs.</description>
                <initializer></initializer>
                <name>event</name>
                <type>QCloseEvent*</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
          </function>
        </access>
        <access>
          <data>
            <type>private slots:</type>
          </data>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Called when an add action is triggered. This creates a new project of the given type and sets it to this window if it has none or else a new main window is created.</description>
              <name>newTriggered</name>
              <operation>Create a new project with the given type.</operation>
              <operation>If this window has no project then set it to the new project.</operation>
              <operation>Else this window already has a project.</operation>
              <operation>Create a new window, setting its project to the new project, and then show it.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description>The project type used to create a new project.</description>
                <initializer></initializer>
                <name>type</name>
                <type>int</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Called when the open action is triggered. This opens a file dialog for the user to select a Socrates Reference project and if successful open it. The open project is set to this window if it has none or a new window otherwise.</description>
              <name>openTriggered</name>
              <operation>Create initialize a file dialog for opening a project file.</operation>
              <operation>Execute the file dialog and make sure it returned accepted.</operation>
              <operation>Get the first file path selected by the user from the file dialog.</operation>
              <operation>Set the current working directory to the parent directory of the selected project.</operation>
              <operation>Open a new project with the file path.</operation>
              <operation>If this window has no project that set it to the opened project.</operation>
              <operation>Else this window already has a project.</operation>
              <operation>Create a new window, setting its project to the opened project, and then show it.</operation>
              <return_description></return_description>
              <type>void</type>
            </data>
          </function>
          <function>
            <data>
              <description>Called when the save action is triggered, calling this window's save method.</description>
              <name>saveTriggered</name>
