                  <description>Returns rich text that displays any properties this view's variable block has set. If this view's variable block has no properties set then this returns an empty string.</description>
                  <name>displayProperties</name>
                  <operation>Create an empty string list, appending any properties this view's variable block has set.</operation>
                  <operation>If the string list is empty then return an empty string.</operation>
                  <operation>Else this view's block has set properties so return a HTML string displaying those set properties.</operation>
                  <return_description>Rich text that displays any properties this view's variable block has set or an empty string if no properties are set.</return_description>
                  <type>QString</type>
                </data>
              </function>
              <function>
                <data>
                  <description>Returns rich text that displays the initial value of this view's variable block. If the variable block has no initial value then an empty string is returned.</description>
                  <name>displayInitializer</name>
                  <operation>Create an empty string.</operation>
                  <operation>Make sure this view's block has an initial value.</operation>
                  <operation>Append a HTML string that displays this view's variable block's initial value, separating that value by the comma delimiter.</operation>
