          <data>
            <description>Moves the child block with the given index up the list by one where the very top of the list is index 0. If the given index is already at the top of the list or out of range then this does nothing.</description>
            <name>moveUp</name>
            <operation>Make sure the given index is within range and not already at the top of the list.</operation>
            <operation>Swap the child pointer at the given index with the pointer directly above it in this block's child list and notify of modification.</operation>
            <operation>Starting with this block iterate up the tree of parents, calling their child moved interface, until the root block is reached or the child moved interface returns false.</operation>
            <return_description></return_description>
            <type>void</type>
          </data>
