              <data>
                <description>The state key for this edit dialog used to keep its qt splitter persistent.</description>
                <initializer></initializer>
                <name>_stateKey</name>
                <type>QString</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
          </access>
        </class>
        <class>
          <data>
            <description>This is the basic block view that displays an associated basic block. Like the basic block it views this class reads in its configuration from an XML element supplied to it from its basic block. The XML definition provides all information about the layout of display elements this view displays. This class can be implemented by another more specialized class and is necessary to do so if the custom viewing element is used.</description>
            <name>View</name>
            <qtobject/>
          </data>
          <parent>
            <data>
              <access>public</access>
              <class>QLabel</class>
            </data>
          </parent>
          <access>
            <data>
              <type>public:</type>
            </data>
            <function>
              <data>
                <description>Constructs a new view with the given basic block which is displays.</description>
                <explicit/>
                <name>^</name>
                <operation>Format this new view's label.</operation>
                <return_description></return_description>
                <type></type>
              </data>
              <variable>
                <data>
                  <description>The basic block this new view is displaying.</description>
                  <initializer></initializer>
                  <name>block</name>
                  <type>const BasicBlock*</type>
                </data>
              </variable>
            </function>
          </access>
          <access>
            <data>
              <type>public slots:</type>
            </data>
            <function>
              <data>
                <description>Updates the label of this view to display its basic block using the view definition provided by it. This overwrites any existing text and replaces it with the new updated version.</description>
                <name>update</name>
                <operation>Create a new string that will hold the new rich text of this view.</operation>
                <operation>Prepare an enumeration and matching string list for recognizing element tag names.</operation>
                <operation>Iterate through all child nodes of this view's basic block's view definition element.</operation>
                <operation>Check to see if the node is an element.</operation>
                <operation>Figure out which display element this is, if any, and add its string to the new updated rich text.</operation>
                <operation>Move to the next node sibling.</operation>
                <operation>Set the text of this view's label to the updated rich text.</operation>
                <return_description></return_description>
                <type>void</type>
              </data>
            </function>
          </access>
          <access>
            <data>
              <type>private:</type>
            </data>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description>The tag name for a header 1 display element, 1 being the largest.</description>
                <initializer>"h1"</initializer>
                <name>_header1Tag</name>
                <static/>
                <type>const char*</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description>The tag name for a header 2 display element, 1 being the largest.</description>
                <initializer>"h2"</initializer>
                <name>_header2Tag</name>
                <static/>
                <type>const char*</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description>The tag name for a header 3 display element, 1 being the largest.</description>
                <initializer>"h3"</initializer>
                <name>_header3Tag</name>
                <static/>
                <type>const char*</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description>The tag name for a paragraphs display element that displays a basic block field as multiple paragraphs separated by double newline characters.</description>
                <initializer>"ps"</initializer>
                <name>_paragraphsTag</name>
                <static/>
                <type>const char*</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description>The tag name for a custom display element specifying a custom method to call that returned a custom string.</description>
                <initializer>"custom"</initializer>
                <name>_customTag</name>
                <static/>
                <type>const char*</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description>The attribute name for the custom method name of a custom display element.</description>
                <initializer>"name"</initializer>
                <name>_nameKey</name>
                <static/>
                <type>const char*</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
          </access>
          <access>
            <data>
              <type>private:</type>
            </data>
            <function>
              <data>
                <description>Adds paragraphs to the given rich text based off the given XML display element definition. If the basic block field referenced by the given display element then nothing will be added. The basic block field referenced must be a string or an exception is thrown.</description>
                <name>addParagraphs</name>
                <operation>Make sure the given display element has the id attribute.</operation>
                <operation>Get the basic block field that the given display element references and make sure it is a string.</operation>
                <operation>Split the basic block field into a string list of paragraphs based off double newline characters being the separator, parsing each string for bold underline markers.</operation>
                <operation>Make sure the list of paragraphs is not empty.</operation>
                <operation>Add the string list to the given rich text as paragraphs.</operation>
                <return_description></return_description>
                <type>void</type>
              </data>
              <variable>
                <data>
                  <description>Pointer to the rich text that paragraphs are added to if the given display element's basic block field is not empty.</description>
                  <initializer></initializer>
                  <name>text</name>
                  <type>QString*</type>
                </data>
              </variable>
              <variable>
                <data>
                  <description>XML display element definition that references the basic block field to add as paragraphs to the given rich text.</description>
                  <initializer></initializer>
                  <name>element</name>
                  <type>const QDomElement&amp;</type>
                </data>
              </variable>
            </function>
            <function>
              <data>
                <description>Adds custom content to the given rich text based off the given XML custom display element. If the provided method name does not exist for this object then an exception is thrown.</description>
                <name>addCustom</name>
                <operation>Lookup the custom method referenced by the name attribute of the given custom display element definition, making sure the method exists.</operation>
                <operation>Invoke the custom method of this object and add the content it returns to the given rich text.</operation>
                <return_description></return_description>
                <type>void</type>
              </data>
              <variable>
                <data>
                  <description>The rich text that custom content is added to.</description>
                  <initializer></initializer>
                  <name>text</name>
                  <type>QString*</type>
                </data>
              </variable>
              <variable>
                <data>
                  <description>XML custom display element definition that provides the custom method name to call and is expected to return a string of custom content.</description>
                  <initializer></initializer>
                  <name>element</name>
                  <type>const QDomElement&amp;</type>
                </data>
              </variable>
            </function>
            <function>
              <data>
                <description>Parses all underline characters from the given list of strings, replacing them with HTML bold tags. The parsed list of strings is returned.</description>
                <name>parseBoldMarkers</name>
                <operation>Create an empty string list that will be returned.</operation>
                <operation>Iterate through all strings of the given string list.</operation>
                <operation>Create an empty parsed string and initialize the ingress state.</operation>
                <operation>Iterate through every character of the text.</operation>
                <operation>Check if the current character is an underline.</operation>
                <operation>Append an opening or closing HTML old tag to the parsed string depending on the ingress state.</operation>
                <operation>Invert the ingress state.</operation>
                <operation>Else the current character is not an underline so simply append it to the parsed string.</operation>
                <operation>Add the parsed string to the list of parsed strings returned.</operation>
                <operation>Return the parsed string list.</operation>
                <return_description>Parsed list of strings, replacing underlines with HTML bold tags.</return_description>
                <type>QStringList</type>
              </data>
              <variable>
                <data>
                  <description>List of strings that is parsed to replace underline characters with HTML bold tags.</description>
                  <initializer></initializer>
                  <name>list</name>
                  <type>const QStringList&amp;</type>
                </data>
              </variable>
            </function>
            <variable>
              <data>
                <description>The basic block that this view is displaying.</description>
                <initializer></initializer>
                <name>_block</name>
                <type>const BasicBlock*</type>
              </data>
            </variable>
          </access>
        </class>
